The Cathedral of the Holy Wives-Myrrh-Bearers in Baku was built in 1909 according to the project of the Russian architect Fedor Mikhailovich Verzhbitsky. Funds for this project were allocated by the Military Ministry of Tsarist Russia, as well as a private donation made by Baku merchant Haji Zeynalabdin Tagiyev. The name of the cathedral has its own history. The cathedral was consecrated in honor of the women who, on the first day after Saturday, came to the Tomb of the resurrected Jesus Christ for ritual smearing of the body with incense and peace. Hence the name of the cathedral in Baku. In 1909, the Cathedral was built for the 206th Salyan Infantry Regiment stationed in Baku.

Церковь была построена по типовому проекту военных храмов, утверждённому Строительной комиссией в 1901 году (арх. Фёдор Михайлович Вержбицкий). Всего в Российской Империи к 1917 году было выстроено не менее 64-х таких церквей. Данный храм для 206-го пехотного Сальянского полка (до 1910 года именовавшегося 262-м пехотным), расквартированного в Баку, был заложен 6 Мая 1908 года, выстроен целиком на средства Военного министерства, и торжественно освящён 6 декабря 1909 года. До этого полк использовал старую полковую Михаило-Архангельскую церковь в центре города, также сохранившуюся доныне. С 1890 года священником этого полка являлся Иоанн Виссарионович Лиадзе (сведения на 1914 год).

The restaurant is located in Monaco and very easy to find. The moment I entered it, I was fascinated by the atmosphere and decoration. We were a group of three and had reserved a table online. Sadly, one part of the menu did not have an English version, but the friendly waitress explained everything in fluent English (which is not expectable in France!). We ordered the lunch set menu and were very satisfied by the chef‘s creations. The combinations were wonderful abd supported the taste.
I‘d like to note that a reservation is highly recommended, eventhough the process might be a little complicated. I can understand that no-shows are irritating, but having customers depositing their credit card for a cancellation fee of 150€ in case late modification of the booking or no-show is an overreaction in my opinion. I think the restaurant should trust customers for calling in advance, if they no they cannot show up.
